        <title>RFC 7349: LDP Hello Cryptographic Authentication, L. Zheng, M. Chen, M. Bhatia</title>
        <dc:date>2014-08-01T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document introduces a new optional Cryptographic Authentication TLV that LDP can use to secure its Hello messages.  It secures the Hello messages against spoofing attacks and some well-known attacks against the IP header.  This document describes a mechanism to secure the LDP Hello messages using Hashed Message Authentication Code (HMAC) with the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) Secure Hash Standard family of algorithms. </description>
    </item>

